video.name: The Best Fudgy BROWNIES RECIPE I Ever Made
video.description:
The ultimate fudgy Brownie Recipe! These homemade brownies are decadent and stay moist for days. There's a secret ingredient that makes them super chocolatey without being overly sweet.
⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️ RECIPE BELOW  ⬇️⬇️⬇️⬇️

BROWNIE RECIPE INGREDIENTS:
►1/2 lb unsalted butter, softened 
►16 oz semisweet chocolate chips, (2 1/2 cups by measuring cup), divided 
►4 large eggs 
►1 Tbsp instant coffee granules (6.2 grams)
►1 Tbsp vanilla extract
►1 1/4 cups granulated sugar 
►2/3 cup all-purpose flour 
►1 1/2 tsp baking powder
►1/2 tsp salt 
►3 Tbsp vegetable oil
►1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder 

🖨 PRINT RECIPE HERE: https://natashaskitchen.com/fudgy-brownie-recipe/

recipeIngredient: 1/2 lb unsalted butter ((softened or cut into pieces if cold for faster melting))
16 oz semisweet chocolate chips ((2 1/2 cups by measuring cup), divided)
3 Tbsp light olive oil  (or vegetable oil)

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat oven to 350˚F. Butter a 9x9 pan and line with parchment paper.
recipeInstructions.name: Preheat oven to 350˚F. Butter a 9x9 pan and line with parchment paper.

recipeInstructions.text: In a medium saucepan over low heat, Melt together 2 cups chocolate chips and butter while whisking then set aside to cool 15 minutes.
recipeInstructions.name: In a medium saucepan over low heat, Melt together 2 cups chocolate chips and butter while whisking then set aside to cool 15 minutes.

recipeInstructions.text: In a second large bowl, whisk together 4 eggs, 1 1/4 cups granulated sugar and coffee granules, 3 Tbsp oil and 1 Tbsp vanilla extract.
recipeInstructions.name: In a second large bowl, whisk together 4 eggs, 1 1/4 cups granulated sugar and coffee granules, 3 Tbsp oil and 1 Tbsp vanilla extract.

recipeInstructions.text: Stir cooled chocolate mixture into the egg mixture.
recipeInstructions.name: Stir cooled chocolate mixture into the egg mixture.

recipeInstructions.text: In a medium bowl, whisk together 2/3 cup flour, 1/2 cup cocoa, 1 1/2 tsp baking powder and 1/2 tsp salt then use a spatula to fold mixture into the batter and fold just until combined. Do not over mix.
recipeInstructions.name: In a medium bowl, whisk together 2/3 cup flour, 1/2 cup cocoa, 1 1/2 tsp baking powder and 1/2 tsp salt then use a spatula to fold mixture into the batter and fold just until combined. Do not over mix.

recipeInstructions.text: Transfer batter to prepared pan and sprinkle all over with remaining 1/2 cup chocolate chips. Bake at 350 for 35-40 min depending on the desired doneness.* Cool until nearly at room temperature then cut into bars before serving.
